article_id:1973,category_name:News,title_name:Japanese-Language Caged Desire Livestream Gifts,image_path:,message:<div>Yumi Uchiyama and Ayaka Asai, voice actors for the Japanese-language version of Dragalia Lost, joined Director Yuji Okada in a livestream of the Caged Desire event that was broadcast in Japanese around <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1612519200"></span>. Thank you to those of you who tuned in to watch!</div><div><br></div><div>The participants were given a set of endeavors during the broadcast that, if completed, would result in rewards being distributed to all players. We&#39;re happy to report that these endeavors were completed successfully, so the following gifts will be sent to players who started playing the game before <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1612524600"></span>.</div><div><br></div><div>■Gifts</div><div>・Wyrmite &times; 1,200</div><div><br></div><div>Note: The gifts can be claimed from your goodie box for up to seven days after reception. If the gifts aren&#39;t retrieved within seven days, they will be lost.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div>,start_time:1612524600,update_time1612523570